WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:02.160
Hello and welcome to Complete Spanish.

00:00:02.160 --> 00:00:13.120
We're really excited about this new material, Language Transfers First Complete course, which is all you need to become a master self-directed language learner and steer yourself to fluency.

00:00:13.059 --> 00:00:19.700
through practice of and exposure to Spanish, enjoying the fascinating journey of delving into language.

00:00:19.700 --> 00:00:23.140
Right after the first hour you will be and feel like

00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:24.480
a Spanish speaker.

00:00:24.480 --> 00:00:33.440
With the thinking method, we are not just interested in teaching you Spanish in record time, but also about exploring the thinking processes, abilities and habits

00:00:33.460 --> 00:00:39.700
which make us effective and confident language learners, in control of our own learning process.

00:00:39.700 --> 00:00:48.260
This will give you a more intimate relationship with your new language and the greater ability to express yourself through the mechanisms that language offers.

00:00:48.320 --> 00:01:02.720
We will reconstruct the language together in a way that will give you all of the know-how to overcome your technical difficulties in that language so that you can concentrate on achieving and enjoying a freedom in your new language.

00:01:02.100 --> 00:01:08.340
The course has been recorded with a volunteer student and is a genuine real-life learning experience.

00:01:08.340 --> 00:01:12.500
The volunteer student does not have a script and she's not acting.

00:01:12.320 --> 00:01:18.800
Recording in this way has allowed us to capture the essence of the learning experience with the thinking method.

00:01:18.800 --> 00:01:26.960
During the length of the course, I will be asking the volunteer student to perform various mental exercises resulting in the construction of sentences.

00:01:27.180 --> 00:01:32.060
When I do so, you will pause the audio and complete the task yourself.

00:01:32.060 --> 00:01:37.179
And then continue listening to see how our volunteer students answered.

00:01:36.939 --> 00:01:42.140
It is important to understand that these are exercises and not tests.

00:01:42.140 --> 00:01:43.899
Do not rush to answer.

00:01:43.899 --> 00:01:45.100
Take your time to think

00:01:45.520 --> 00:01:57.920
through your answer at your own pace, building it up piece by piece with the instructions you receive during the audio, which are as much about the language as they are about the mental processes.

00:01:57.820 --> 00:02:02.060
It is very important that you don't try to memorize anything.

00:02:02.060 --> 00:02:09.100
Memorization is an extremely distracting process and I need you 100% here with us.

00:02:08.860 --> 00:02:17.900
If you need help getting over any anxiety about forgetting or the possibility of forgetting, then just remind yourself that you can always repeat the course at the end.

00:02:17.900 --> 00:02:18.860
So relax

00:02:19.420 --> 00:02:22.700
It's also important that you don't write anything down.

00:02:22.700 --> 00:02:27.260
You will carry around your new language in your head, not in a notebook

00:02:27.060 --> 00:02:31.379
Some of the content you may forget, and that's okay, that's part of the design.

00:02:31.379 --> 00:02:39.700
Don't worry about that and just concentrate on understanding, not memorizing, the explanations and building the sentences we give you

00:02:39.820 --> 00:02:47.820
Find the time and place to do the audios where you are calm, undisturbed and can concentrate solely on your language learning experience.

00:02:47.820 --> 00:02:54.300
Using headphones should help you to tune out from the outside world and concentrate on this experience.

00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:57.120
Try to be well rested when you do the courses.

00:02:57.120 --> 00:03:03.120
The tired mind makes all kinds of unproductive shortcuts and careless mistakes.

00:03:03.020 --> 00:03:10.780
It is of the utmost importance that you don't just listen to the audios, even if you're listening and understanding the process

00:03:10.840 --> 00:03:20.280
but that you pause every time I ask our volunteer student a question and work it out for yourself before hearing her response.

00:03:20.120 --> 00:03:26.920
Otherwise, you will not have your own language learning experience, you will just be witnessing somebody else's.

00:03:26.920 --> 00:03:34.120
If you do not pause and work out the answer for yourself before continuing, you will finish knowing a lot about Spanish.

00:03:33.920 --> 00:03:35.920
but not speaking Spanish.

00:03:35.920 --> 00:03:40.240
Sometimes our student takes one second to reply, sometimes thirty seconds or more.

00:03:40.240 --> 00:03:48.560
What we've done in the editing process is to leave a short pause for you to hit the pause button and then embark on your own mental journey.

00:03:48.060 --> 00:03:52.220
before replying out loud and continuing with us.

00:03:52.220 --> 00:03:56.459
The more energy you have, the more information you will naturally assimilate

00:03:56.260 --> 00:04:03.460
If you find yourself tuning out during the explanations due to tiredness, then take a break and go back to it later.

00:04:03.460 --> 00:04:07.700
It's better to do little often than a lot all at once

00:04:07.540 --> 00:04:14.500
So 20 minutes a day you will find much more effective than a few hours crammed in over the weekend.

00:04:14.500 --> 00:04:20.660
But of course, you will find your own balance with other commitments and how quickly you wish to learn Spanish

00:04:20.920 --> 00:04:28.920
If it's been a while since you've had to concentrate, then don't worry, you will notice your concentration span increase very rapidly.

00:04:28.840 --> 00:04:32.360
And remember, think slowly to learn quickly.

00:04:32.360 --> 00:04:39.480
This isn't at school where we expect your hand to go up straight away with the correct answer through memorization.

00:04:39.260 --> 00:04:52.220
This is a different process where you are expected to take the time to think your answer through and to appreciate and understand that it's those very processes of taking that time and thinking those answers.

00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:55.280
through which makes us assimilate this new knowledge.

00:04:55.280 --> 00:05:02.560
You don't even have to worry about memorizing this advice because it will be revisited many times during the course

00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:10.560
Not only are all the courses at Language Transfer available for free download, but we are also an unfunded and independent project.

00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:17.120
This allows us to create the best courses we can create without external monetary or publicity pressures.

00:05:16.520 --> 00:05:24.600
Now to maintain this freedom and to continue with the many plans we have in the pipeline for more audio courses and also textbooks.

00:05:24.740 --> 00:05:27.060
We really do need help with donations.

00:05:27.060 --> 00:05:30.980
So if you love the course and are in a position to donate, then please do.

00:05:30.980 --> 00:05:34.340
Many thanks for joining us and let's begin.

